      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of April 8 Chess column; suspension of Steve Rosenberg by United States Chess Federation for wearing wireless receiver is not in effect because Rosenberg is appealing</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Chess column last Sunday, about the effect of technology on cheating, included incorrect information from the United States Chess Federation about Steve Rosenberg, a player who was expelled from the World Open last July after a tournament director said he found a wireless receiver in Mr. Rosenberg's ear. Although the federation's ethics committee has indeed ordered that he be suspended from playing in tournaments, that suspension is not in effect because Mr. Rosenberg is appealing. His case will be heard in August.</p>
      </block>
